wikipedia_page.main: Sylvia Jackson (born 12 June 1945) is a British sprint canoer who competed in the late 1960s. She was eliminated in the semifinals in the K-1 500 m event at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City.

response: Dr Sylvia Jackson (born 3 December 1946) is a Scottish Labour Party politician, and former Member of the Scottish Parliament (MSP).
